Saudi Arabia  has granted nine real
estate developers licenses to sell off-plan properties in the
kingdom, the  Saudi Press Agency  reported, citing Commerce
Undersecretary Hassan Bin Fadl Aqil.  The license gives a company the right to place
advertisements to market and sell real-estate units that havenâ€™t
yet been built and to deposit all payments made by potential
buyers into a local escrow bank account, according to the news
service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
